mibnatProfileTable.name: mibnatProfileTable

natProfile_NatRouting.name: natProfile_NatRouting
natProfile_NatRouting.description: A boolean. When set to TRUE it translates all the lan addresses to dynamicaly assigned internet address.

natProfile_NatProfile.name: natProfile_NatProfile
natProfile_NatProfile.description: The name of this NAT profile, used in other types of profiles to refer to this NAT profile.

natProfile_NatLan.name: natProfile_NatLan

natProfile_FrameRelayAddress.name: natProfile_FrameRelayAddress
natProfile_FrameRelayAddress.description: The Frame Relay/ATM VC user assigned IP address

natProfile_StickyAddress.name: natProfile_StickyAddress
natProfile_StickyAddress.description: A Boolen. When set to TRUE enables the sticky IP address feature - the router will try to retain the last IP address it got from the host by negotiating it with the host.

natProfile_StickyTimeout.name: natProfile_StickyTimeout
natProfile_StickyTimeout.description: A number. Represents the number of minutes the router will try to request the sticky IP address counting from the end of the last session.

natProfile_NoNatAddress.name: natProfile_NoNatAddress
natProfile_NoNatAddress.description: Address of subnet which should be exempted from Network Address Translation. An address of 0.0.0.0 means that selective NAT is disabled.

natProfile_AlternateNaptAddress.name: natProfile_AlternateNaptAddress
natProfile_AlternateNaptAddress.description: Public address to use on the WAN for sindle-address NAT instead of the address negotiated via IPCP. A value of 0.0.0.0 means use the address negotiated via IPCP.

natProfile_NaptIdleTcpTimeout.name: natProfile_NaptIdleTcpTimeout
natProfile_NaptIdleTcpTimeout.description: The flush timer interval in minutes for idle TCP connection entries in the NAPT table. Defaults to 24 hours.

natProfile_NatAddrPoolNum.name: natProfile_NatAddrPoolNum
natProfile_NatAddrPoolNum.description: Designates the address pool to use for Address Pool NAT.
